WEBVTT

00:03.503 --> 00:04.587
(Elka)
<i>Hot in Cleveland</i> is recorded

00:04.671 --> 00:06.798
in front
of a live studio audience.

00:06.881 --> 00:09.259
{\an5}(male TV announcer)
The Cincinnati Bengals
are at their own one-yard line,

00:09.342 --> 00:12.220
and barring a miracle, this game
belongs to the Cleveland Browns.

00:12.303 --> 00:15.765
Well, that must make
you happy, huh, Elka?

00:15.849 --> 00:18.059
{\an1}She's on the phone
with the mayor of Cincinnati.

00:18.143 --> 00:20.311
{\an1}She bet him
that if Cleveland wins,

00:20.395 --> 00:22.439
{\an1}he has to wear
the Browns mascot costume

00:22.522 --> 00:26.276
{\an1}for a week
and dress like a dog.

00:26.359 --> 00:31.906
I hope that costume
won't be too ruff on you.

00:31.990 --> 00:34.576
{\an5}(TV announcer)
And it's Dalton to Jones,
and he's down.

00:34.659 --> 00:36.286
No, a lateral to Bernard,

00:36.369 --> 00:37.370
and he's up!

00:37.454 --> 00:38.121
They're not gonna catch him!

00:38.204 --> 00:39.789
What? No!

00:39.873 --> 00:41.750
(TV announcer)
Touchdown! It's a miracle!

00:41.833 --> 00:42.792
The Bengals win!

00:42.876 --> 00:44.836
The Bengals win!

00:44.919 --> 00:47.922
That was amazing.

00:48.006 --> 00:52.635
I mean, boo.

00:52.719 --> 00:54.053
{\an1}I guess you lost the bet,
huh?

00:54.137 --> 00:57.515
I've never been a loser
before.

00:57.599 --> 01:00.310
How do you guys do it?

01:02.896 --> 01:05.857
[door bell rings]

01:09.444 --> 01:11.821
- Hi, baby.
- Hey, babe.

01:11.905 --> 01:14.491
{\an1}Oh, weird.

01:14.574 --> 01:18.286
It's like kissing my mom.

01:18.369 --> 01:20.789
You kiss your mom that way?

01:20.872 --> 01:22.665
No, it's just that you're
wearing the same perfume

01:22.749 --> 01:23.792
my mom wears.

01:23.875 --> 01:25.168
Oh, yeah, I was at
the mall today,

01:25.251 --> 01:26.795
and some girl asked me
if I like Shalimar,

01:26.878 --> 01:29.422
and while I was trying to
remember if it was a disco band

01:29.506 --> 01:32.550
or a perfume, she got me.

01:32.634 --> 01:33.593
I'll go wash it off.

01:33.676 --> 01:35.011
Don't use the kitchen sink.

01:35.094 --> 01:36.638
It's leaking.
We need to call a plumber.

01:36.721 --> 01:37.722
(Dane)
You don't need a plumber.

01:37.806 --> 01:39.140
You got the guy right here.

01:39.224 --> 01:43.019
(Bob)
Two guys.

01:43.102 --> 01:44.854
I didn't realize
you were the handy type.

01:44.938 --> 01:46.147
(Bob)
Are you kidding?

01:46.231 --> 01:47.315
Yeah, when I was a kid,
I used to help

01:47.398 --> 01:49.025
my dad fix stuff
all the time.

01:49.108 --> 01:50.068
So you want
me to grab you a beer

01:50.151 --> 01:54.405
or just go play
in the back yard?

01:54.489 --> 01:55.824
Isn't Bob adorable?

01:55.907 --> 01:58.493
Oh, I'm so in love with him.

01:58.576 --> 02:01.204
I think I'm ready to give him
the <i> Love, Actually</i> test.

02:01.287 --> 02:04.707
Joy, you know the reason
every guy fails that test?

02:04.791 --> 02:06.584
It's because guys
don't like <i> Love, Actually.</i>

02:06.668 --> 02:08.711
Bob is not like other guys.

02:08.794 --> 02:10.713
I believe he is the one guy

02:10.797 --> 02:14.717
who will love that movie
as much as I do.

02:14.801 --> 02:19.097
Doesn't Bob remind you
a little bit of Colin Firth?

02:19.180 --> 02:23.101
Yeah, you really are in love.

02:23.184 --> 02:24.686
What a disaster.

02:24.769 --> 02:26.187
A week before my play opens,

02:26.271 --> 02:29.691
and my costar totally screws me
and leaves the show.

02:29.774 --> 02:30.775
What happened?

02:30.859 --> 02:34.654
Oh, his appendix burst.

02:34.737 --> 02:37.574
Where are we gonna find a
masculine Stanley Kowalski type

02:37.657 --> 02:40.243
in his 40s in such little time?

02:40.326 --> 02:44.372
Just letting you know
I turned the water off.

02:44.455 --> 02:46.207
{\an3}And I helped out
with the whole righty-tighty,

02:46.291 --> 02:49.711
lefty-loosy business.

02:49.794 --> 02:51.588
Excuse me,
have you ever acted?

02:51.671 --> 02:55.592
{\an3}I was the star
in a Nativity play once,

02:55.675 --> 02:58.219
literally the star.

02:58.303 --> 03:03.057
{\an3}Ah, but you weren't
talking to me.

03:03.141 --> 03:05.810
Me? Oh, I haven't acted
before.

03:05.894 --> 03:07.770
Oh, but honey, you could.

03:07.854 --> 03:09.439
You should be
in Victoria's play.

03:09.522 --> 03:10.773
I mean,
you're between jobs right now,

03:10.857 --> 03:13.610
{\an1}and this might be just the thing
to get you going.

03:13.693 --> 03:14.736
And you look like an actor.

03:14.819 --> 03:15.778
I mean, that's half of it.

03:15.862 --> 03:19.407
80%, really.

03:19.490 --> 03:21.659
{\an3}I'm afraid
I would embarrass myself.

03:21.743 --> 03:24.454
Come on. On my radio show,
I am always telling people,

03:24.537 --> 03:27.123
{\an1}fears about embarrassment
almost never come true.

03:27.206 --> 03:28.499
{\an3}(Elka)
Not in this case.

03:39.010 --> 03:40.970
I know I'm 18 days
into a juice fast,

03:41.054 --> 03:45.808
but is anyone else
seeing Elka

03:45.892 --> 03:48.102
in a tiger suit?

03:48.186 --> 03:49.854
She has to dress
like the mascot

03:49.938 --> 03:51.773
{\an1}of the Cincinnati Bengals
for a whole week

03:51.856 --> 03:53.358
because she lost a bet.

03:53.441 --> 03:55.985
{\an3}And I'm scheduled
to be on <i> The Grill</i> this week.

03:56.069 --> 03:57.695
<i>The Grill</i> with Arnie McManus?

03:57.779 --> 03:59.322
I love that show.

03:59.405 --> 04:01.032
He's always taking
politicians down.

04:04.953 --> 04:09.791
{\an3}I'm a politician,
you idiot.

04:09.874 --> 04:11.960
{\an3}Well, normally I'd be upset
when someone calls me an idiot,

04:12.043 --> 04:15.296
{\an3}but in that tiger suit,
well, she's just so adorable.

04:21.970 --> 04:25.515
Oh, it's gonna be a long week.

04:27.600 --> 04:29.894
[upbeat music]

04:29.978 --> 04:32.188
♪ Ba-ba, Ba-ba ♪

04:32.271 --> 04:35.191
♪ Ba-ba, Ba-ba ♪

04:35.274 --> 04:37.068
♪ Hey! ♪

04:37.151 --> 04:39.779
{\an8}I just came to watch.

04:42.448 --> 04:43.908
{\an8}I ordered room service.

04:43.992 --> 04:45.034
{\an8}Are you hungry?

04:45.118 --> 04:47.704
{\an8}Hungry for you.

04:47.787 --> 04:52.542
{\an8}Kiss me, Marnie.

04:52.625 --> 04:55.378
{\an8}What the--

04:55.461 --> 04:59.215
{\an8}Stop it.

04:59.298 --> 05:01.009
{\an7}Your girlfriend doesn't
kiss you like that, does she?

05:01.092 --> 05:06.431
{\an9}I wouldn't be here
if she did.

05:06.514 --> 05:09.350
{\an8}Their chemistry is amazing.

05:09.434 --> 05:11.728
{\an8}Everyone thinks
they must be doing it.

05:11.811 --> 05:14.605
{\an8}Well, they're not
because that's my boyfriend

05:14.689 --> 05:15.606
{\an8}and my best friend.

05:15.690 --> 05:17.859
{\an8}Oh, just like in the play.

05:17.942 --> 05:19.736
{\an8}Yeah, yeah.

05:19.819 --> 05:22.613
{\an8}Just like in the play.

05:22.697 --> 05:23.948
{\an8}That was great.

05:24.032 --> 05:25.283
{\an8}Now let's go again,
but remember to show

05:25.366 --> 05:27.744
{\an8}that insatiable hunger
you have for each other.

05:27.827 --> 05:28.786
{\an8}I want to see more heat.

05:28.870 --> 05:32.123
{\an8}More?

05:32.206 --> 05:34.542
{\an7}Sorry.
Hi, honey.

05:36.669 --> 05:41.382
{\an7}Oh, my god, Melanie,
acting is such a rush.

05:41.466 --> 05:43.760
{\an9}Yeah, yeah, but all that
kissing with Victoria,

05:43.843 --> 05:45.470
{\an8}it almost seemed real.

05:45.553 --> 05:46.763
{\an8}It was real.

05:46.846 --> 05:48.598
{\an8}I'm sorry, what?

05:48.681 --> 05:50.433
{\an8}For my character.

05:50.516 --> 05:54.103
{\an7}My character
really was kissing Victoria.

05:54.187 --> 05:56.314
But aren't you your character?

05:56.397 --> 05:59.984
{\an1}Let me explain to you
how acting works, Melanie.

06:00.068 --> 06:01.652
{\an1}My character says
he's a painter.

06:01.736 --> 06:04.489
{\an1}Does that make Dane
a painter, too?

06:04.572 --> 06:07.450
{\an1}No.

06:07.533 --> 06:12.789
{\an1}Until he walks out there
on that stage, and then yes,

06:12.872 --> 06:14.999
he's a painter.

06:15.083 --> 06:18.795
{\an3}Got it,
but about all that kissing.

06:18.878 --> 06:21.923
{\an1}Does Dane get sexually excited
when he kisses Victoria?

06:22.006 --> 06:24.175
{\an1}No.

06:24.258 --> 06:27.136
{\an1}But when my character
kisses Victoria...

06:27.220 --> 06:31.265
{\an1}oh, yeah.

06:31.349 --> 06:34.769
Well, that really
clears things up.

06:34.852 --> 06:37.146
There she is.

06:37.230 --> 06:41.192
{\an1}Look at her, beauty,
brains, funny.

06:41.275 --> 06:45.363
{\an1}You never get all three
in the same package.

06:45.446 --> 06:48.157
No, you do not.

06:48.241 --> 06:49.826
Hello, Victoria.

06:49.909 --> 06:51.244
Can I get you a drink?

06:51.327 --> 06:53.287
{\an3}I'll have a glass
of merlot.

06:53.371 --> 06:55.331
{\an1}Okay.

06:55.414 --> 06:58.793
{\an1}Wow. Melanie,
your boyfriend is a natural.

06:58.876 --> 07:00.294
I was freaked out
about opening night,

07:00.378 --> 07:02.004
but now I can't wait.

07:02.088 --> 07:04.006
The critics are gonna love us.

07:04.090 --> 07:06.509
But you know,
it's a little unsettling

07:06.592 --> 07:08.970
watching someone you're crazy
about kissing someone else.

07:09.053 --> 07:11.347
Mel, it's just acting.

07:11.430 --> 07:13.015
{\an3}Yeah, but you really
seemed into it.

07:13.099 --> 07:15.518
{\an1}No, I'm not,
but my character.

07:15.601 --> 07:18.980
{\an1}[purrs]

07:19.063 --> 07:20.731
Let me explain how acting works.

07:20.815 --> 07:24.986
I know how acting works!

07:25.069 --> 07:27.738
[melodramatic piano plays
on TV]

07:29.115 --> 07:31.742
So that was <i> Love, Actually.</i>

07:31.826 --> 07:33.202
What did you think?

07:33.286 --> 07:36.205
{\an1}I loved it.
Sweet and funny.

07:36.289 --> 07:38.207
- Just like you.
- Aw.

07:38.291 --> 07:40.751
{\an3}Melanie said no guy would like
it, but I knew you would.

07:40.835 --> 07:42.253
Oh, of course.

07:42.336 --> 07:46.048
{\an1}I mean, what a cast,
Hugh Grant, Liam Neeson,

07:46.132 --> 07:48.217
Snape from <i> Harry Potter.</i>

07:53.681 --> 07:55.725
{\an3}Shall we continue
this <i> Love, Actually</i> discussion

07:55.808 --> 07:56.851
{\an3}upstairs?

07:56.934 --> 08:00.271
Yes, actually.

08:00.354 --> 08:04.358
- Let's get some wine.
- All right.

08:04.442 --> 08:05.735
Elka, what are you doing here?

08:05.818 --> 08:07.570
Isn't this your bowling night?

08:07.653 --> 08:11.407
I'm not leaving this house
until this bet is over.

08:11.490 --> 08:14.619
Now, get off my tail.

08:14.702 --> 08:16.245
Okay, I'm sorry.

08:16.329 --> 08:20.458
{\an3}No, you're standing
on my tail.

08:20.541 --> 08:21.125
{\an3}Well, you're gonna
have to leave the house

08:21.209 --> 08:23.085
to appear on <i> The Grill.</i>

08:23.169 --> 08:24.962
No, I don't.
I postponed.

08:25.046 --> 08:27.089
Because of the suit?

08:27.173 --> 08:30.593
Plus I've got a few things
I don't want to be asked about.

08:30.676 --> 08:32.470
Like how you're still
living here

08:32.553 --> 08:37.433
and renting out
the mayor's mansion on AirBnB?

08:37.515 --> 08:41.312
I've got a wedding
coming in next week.

08:41.395 --> 08:43.397
{\an3}Arnie's gonna kill you
on <i> The Grill.</i>

08:43.481 --> 08:45.399
He already has.

08:45.483 --> 08:47.235
They've been
running his promo all day.

08:50.029 --> 08:53.574
Mayor Elka Ostrovsky,
why are you avoiding me?

08:53.658 --> 08:56.452
Are you too busy making
silly bets to hop on <i> The Grill</i>

08:56.535 --> 08:58.538
and answer the tough questions?

08:58.621 --> 09:02.416
Or to put it another way,
is the tiger chicken?

09:04.710 --> 09:06.337
{\an1}I agree you shouldn't go
on the show,

09:06.420 --> 09:07.964
but isn't hiding out here

09:08.047 --> 09:11.467
{\an1}worse than taking
a little public teasing?

09:11.550 --> 09:14.136
You're right.

09:14.220 --> 09:17.139
I'm gonna go out there
and take my medicine.

09:17.223 --> 09:20.643
{\an1}You're going to the bar,
aren't you?

09:20.726 --> 09:22.186
That's where they keep
my medicine.

09:28.234 --> 09:30.820
{\an1}I think Dane's falling in love
with Victoria.

09:30.903 --> 09:31.988
Oh, I'm sure he's not.

09:32.071 --> 09:32.989
It's just the play.

09:33.072 --> 09:35.283
The play is the problem.

09:35.366 --> 09:36.993
Melanie,
if you want my advice,

09:37.076 --> 09:39.161
this is a trust issue.

09:39.245 --> 09:40.830
That's where I'm lucky with Bob.

09:40.913 --> 09:44.792
The only thing I ever wanted
from him was complete honesty,

09:44.875 --> 09:47.211
and he's given me that.

09:47.295 --> 09:50.715
How does that address
my problem?

09:50.798 --> 09:54.885
I guess it doesn't.

09:54.969 --> 09:57.513
I'm gonna call Bob and tell him
how much I love him.

09:57.596 --> 10:00.725
And look,
there's a message from him.

10:00.808 --> 10:01.851
See how in sync we are?

10:01.934 --> 10:04.186
Amazing.

10:04.270 --> 10:07.690
{\an5}(Bob voicemail)
Actually, Dr. Cutler, it's been
a pretty good week for me.

10:07.773 --> 10:11.193
He must have butt-dialed me
from his therapist's office.

10:11.277 --> 10:16.532
{\an3}This is the holy grail
of snooping on your boyfriend.

10:16.615 --> 10:18.826
{\an5}(Bob voicemail)
Things are going great
with Joy,

10:18.909 --> 10:21.203
except she made me sit
through this misshapen freak

10:21.287 --> 10:23.914
of a movie called
<i>Love, Actually.</i>

10:23.998 --> 10:25.708
He said he loved it.

10:25.791 --> 10:26.751
{\an5}(Bob voicemail)
If I wanted to be tortured
for two hours,

10:26.834 --> 10:31.005
I'd take a Pilates class.

10:31.088 --> 10:32.840
Anyway, about my hopes and dre--

10:32.923 --> 10:35.343
{\an3}Who cares?

10:35.426 --> 10:38.012
Can you believe
Bob lied to me?

10:38.095 --> 10:40.890
He's a liar like every
other man I've dated.

10:40.973 --> 10:42.558
What are you gonna do?

10:42.641 --> 10:44.018
{\an3}I'm gonna torture him
with Pilates

10:44.101 --> 10:48.022
{\an3}until he confesses
he's a liar.

10:48.105 --> 10:49.899
Bob's still trainable.

10:49.982 --> 10:53.069
{\an3}I'm gonna break him
like a puppy.

10:53.152 --> 10:55.363
Dane is like a puppy
with this acting thing.

10:55.446 --> 10:57.615
He just wants to put his mouth
on everything,

10:57.698 --> 11:00.576
especially Victoria.

11:00.659 --> 11:03.954
{\an3}If only there was some puppy
repellant we could spray on her.

11:04.038 --> 11:07.416
{\an1}There is, Dane's mother's
perfume, Shalimar.

11:07.500 --> 11:08.751
He'll still have to kiss her,

11:08.834 --> 11:10.544
but he'll hate
every second of it.

11:10.628 --> 11:13.089
All I have to do is spray it
on Victoria's costume.

11:13.172 --> 11:15.424
That's a brilliant idea.

11:15.508 --> 11:16.967
You know, most girlfriends

11:17.051 --> 11:21.430
{\an3}wouldn't care enough
to go as far as we do.

11:21.514 --> 11:24.100
They're lucky to have us.

11:24.183 --> 11:26.435
[helicopter blades whirring]

11:26.519 --> 11:27.978
Oh, my goodness.

11:28.062 --> 11:30.606
Why is there a helicopter
landing on our front lawn?

11:33.317 --> 11:34.735
Thanks, LeBron.

11:39.240 --> 11:41.784
This suit is magic.

11:41.867 --> 11:44.829
LeBron James just dropped you
off in his helicopter.

11:44.912 --> 11:47.915
Well, first we
stopped in Atlantic City.

11:47.998 --> 11:50.459
- I won big.
- What?

11:50.543 --> 11:54.505
I was counting cards out loud.

11:54.588 --> 11:56.966
They didn't care.

11:57.049 --> 11:58.926
So I guess
you're not hiding anymore?

11:59.009 --> 12:02.680
I'm bulletproof, which is
why I'm going on <i> The Grill.</i>

12:02.763 --> 12:05.808
Elka, Arnie McManus
will eat you alive.

12:05.891 --> 12:07.977
I got this.

12:08.060 --> 12:10.604
I also got this.

12:10.688 --> 12:13.441
{\an1}Is that LeBron James'
championship ring?

12:13.524 --> 12:15.443
Not anymore.

12:20.239 --> 12:22.032
I'm so glad you like Pilates.

12:22.116 --> 12:23.451
Are you kidding?

12:23.534 --> 12:26.120
{\an3}I love it.

12:26.203 --> 12:30.332
{\an3}It's fantastic, the way
it's stretching my groin.

12:30.416 --> 12:33.794
{\an3}I can't believe there was a time
I didn't do it.

12:33.878 --> 12:37.673
Oh, just thinking
about that time now.

12:37.756 --> 12:40.301
So you're really enjoying it?

12:40.384 --> 12:44.346
Yeah, it's so much fun.

12:44.430 --> 12:46.140
- Liar.
- What?

12:46.223 --> 12:47.850
You lied to me about Pilates,

12:47.933 --> 12:50.352
the same way you lied
to me about <i> Love, Actually.</i>

12:50.436 --> 12:51.687
How do you know that?

12:51.770 --> 12:54.732
I mean, why would you say that?

12:54.815 --> 12:59.487
Because you butt-dialed me
from your therapy session.

12:59.570 --> 13:03.157
And you listened?

13:03.240 --> 13:04.867
Don't change the subject.

13:04.950 --> 13:06.368
You violated my trust.

13:06.452 --> 13:10.456
{\an3}Well, what about
my trust, huh?

13:10.539 --> 13:11.999
{\an3}Listening in
on a therapy session

13:12.082 --> 13:14.043
{\an3}is way worse than pretending
to like some stupid movie.

13:14.126 --> 13:15.544
Stupid movie?

13:15.628 --> 13:17.213
Yes, stupid movie.

13:17.296 --> 13:19.548
{\an3}Some creepy stalker holding up
a bunch of dumb cue cards

13:19.632 --> 13:20.883
for the woman he loves?

13:20.966 --> 13:22.092
What's romantic about that?

13:22.176 --> 13:23.552
How about everything?

13:23.636 --> 13:25.554
That's only my favorite scene.

13:25.638 --> 13:27.264
The point is, you lied,

13:27.348 --> 13:29.517
{\an1}and if you lied about this,
what else have you lied about?

13:29.600 --> 13:32.728
{\an3}No, the point is you
eavesdropped, and I'm furious.

13:32.811 --> 13:34.605
{\an3}I'm gonna need you
to storm out right now.

13:34.688 --> 13:35.898
Me? Why should I storm out?

13:35.981 --> 13:37.399
Why don't you storm out?

13:37.483 --> 13:39.026
{\an3}Because I also lied about
how good it felt

13:39.109 --> 13:40.319
to stretch my groin.

13:48.994 --> 13:50.454
Well, I did it.

13:50.538 --> 13:52.706
{\an1}Not only did I spray Victoria's
costume with Shalimar,

13:52.790 --> 13:54.291
{\an1}but I doused Dane's
in Old Spice,

13:54.375 --> 13:56.210
{\an1}which is the cologne
that Victoria's dad wears.

13:56.293 --> 13:59.380
{\an1}It's gonna be like they're
kissing their parents.

13:59.463 --> 14:00.714
Where's Bob?

14:00.798 --> 14:02.383
I don't think he's coming.

14:02.466 --> 14:03.759
I found the love of my life

14:03.842 --> 14:06.303
and I pushed him away
with my stupid scheme

14:06.387 --> 14:07.429
